            <Text>ⓘ GDP = Σ weighted yields × turn × 1M  ·  hover for explanation</Text>
        </Row>
        <Row Tag="LOC_DEMOGRAPHICS_CAPTION_GDP_TITLE">
            <Text>Gross Domestic Product</Text>
        </Row>
        <Row Tag="LOC_DEMOGRAPHICS_CAPTION_GDP_BODY">
            <Text>&lt;p&gt;A pseudo-realistic value combining a civilization's per-turn yields, weighted by how much each yield contributes to a real economy.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Formula:&lt;/b&gt; Σ (yield × weight) × turn × 1,000,000&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Weights&lt;/b&gt; (per yield point):&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Gold&lt;/b&gt; — 1.0 (currency = direct trade)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Production&lt;/b&gt; — 1.0 (industrial output)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Science&lt;/b&gt; — 1.2 (innovation compounds over time)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Culture&lt;/b&gt; — 1.2 (soft power &amp; tourism)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Food&lt;/b&gt; — 0.5 (subsistence; only the surplus is GDP-like)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Influence&lt;/b&gt; — 1.5 (diplomatic / treaty leverage)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Why multiply by turn?&lt;/b&gt; Real economies compound: a civ at turn 200 with the same per-turn yields as a civ at turn 50 represents 4× the accumulated economic mass.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Presentational only — never affects game state.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</Text>
        </Row>
        <Row Tag="LOC_DEMOGRAPHICS_CAPTION_APPROVAL_TRIGGER">
            <Text>ⓘ Diplomatic Approval = Σ relationship-weighted scores  ·  hover for explanation</Text>
        </Row>
        <Row Tag="LOC_DEMOGRAPHICS_CAPTION_APPROVAL_TITLE">
            <Text>Diplomatic Approval — international reputation</Text>
        </Row>
        <Row Tag="LOC_DEMOGRAPHICS_CAPTION_APPROVAL_BODY">
            <Text>&lt;p&gt;A signed aggregate of how every other civilization currently feels about you. Goes &lt;b&gt;up&lt;/b&gt; when you have allies and friends; goes &lt;b&gt;down&lt;/b&gt; when you're surrounded by hostiles or at war.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Per-major-civ contribution&lt;/b&gt; (based on the relationship enum the diplomacy screen shows):&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Alliance&lt;/b&gt; — +5&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Helpful&lt;/b&gt; — +3&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Friendly&lt;/b&gt; — +2&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Neutral&lt;/b&gt; — 0&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Unfriendly&lt;/b&gt; — −2&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Hostile&lt;/b&gt; — −3&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;At War&lt;/b&gt; — −5&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;City-state contribution:&lt;/b&gt; +2 per CS where you are suzerain, dampened by 0.3× (so CS-heavy strategies don't dwarf major-civ relations).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Score = Σ(major weights) + 0.3 × Σ(suzerain bonuses)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Sampled each turn from each civ's perspective on the local player. Presentational only.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</Text>
        </Row>
